|| 2 || 0 || A supercell formed above Belgium going north passing Amsterdam where 1 EF-0 crossed streets where people where shopping, later on around Hoorn 3 funnel clouds where reported. After another 25&nbsp;km a Tornado formed above farmland destroying a farm with EF-4 Damage, no animal or human got injured. .{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} {{Tornado chart small| F0 = 1| F1 = 0| F2 = 0| F3 = 0| F4 = 1| F5 = 0| Enhanced =no }} |- | Sonnac Tornado || 16 September 2015 || [[Sonnac, Charente-Maritime|Sonnac]], [[France]] || 5 || / || A long track F2 tornado struck many villages in France on 70,2&nbsp;km path. In Sonnac some houses were badly damaged. On the same day 4 other tornadoes struck in Belgium and Luxembourg where a person was injured.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} {{Tornado chart small| F0 = 0| F1 = 3| F2 = 2| F3 = 0| F4 = 0| F5 = 0| Enhanced =no }} |- | Russia Tornado Outbreak|| 14 May 2016 || [[Luhansk Oblast]]- [[Ukraine]], [[Rostov Oblast]], [[Stavropol Oblast]] and [[Volgograd Oblast]] – [[Russia]] || 15 || 5 injuries || A long track F3 tornado struck many villages in Rostov Oblast on 56&nbsp;km path injuring 5 people.Other tornadoes were reported but most of them remain on open field.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} {{Tornado chart small| F0 = 4| F1 = 2| F2 = 1| F3 = 1| F4 = 0| F5 = 0| Enhanced =no }} |- | Eastern Europe Outbreak || 11–14 July 2016 || [[Belarus]], [[Russia]] and [[Poland]] || 10 || 2 || 4 Tornadoes over Belarus, Russia and Poland on 11 July, 2 of which F2 tornadoes. One F1 tornado in Belarus on 12th and the next day there were 3 tornadoes, two in Belarus and one in Russia, the last one was an F3 tornado that travelled for 44&nbsp;km and killed 2 people. On 14th an F0 tornado touched ground in Poland.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} {{Tornado chart small| F0 = 1| F1 = 2| F2 = 3| F3 = 1| F4 = 0| F5 = 0| Enhanced =no }} |- | Russia Tornado Outbreak || 24 August 2016 || [[Russia]] || 1 || 0 || One F1 tornado over