980951000205X A systematic approach to synoptic tornado climatology of Hungary for the recent years (1996–2001) based on official damage reports http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0169809506001219 Towards a European climatology of meteorological parameters associated to the genesis of severe storms http://eng.tethys.cat/files/3tethys-02-eng.pdf European climatology of severe convective storm environmental parameters: A test for significant tornado events http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0169809506001360 * Doe, R. (2003) Devastating tornadoes in Cyprus 27 January 2003. Int. J. Meteorol., 28, pp. 242–245 * Reynolds, D.J., 1999: European tornado climatology, 1960–1989. J. Meteorol. 24 (244), pp. 376–403 * Simeonov P., Bocheva L., Marinova T., 2009: Severe convective storms phenomena occurrence during the warm half of the year in Bulgaria (1961–2006). Atmos. Res. 93, 498–505. * Sioutas, M. V. (2002) Damaging tornadoes in Greece: July and September 2001. J. Meteorol., UK, 27, pp. 17–22 * Wegner, W. A., 1917, Wind- und Wasserhosen in Europa. Vieweg und Sohn, Braunschweig, Germany, (1917). 301 pp. http://www.tordach.org/papers.htm http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/01698095/67 -->
