{{italic title}}
'''''The Classical Gazetteer''''' is a short descriptive geographical dictionary by [[William Hazlitt (registrar)|William Hazlitt]] (son of the critic [[William Hazlitt]]), written in 1851 and containing 15,000  places of [[Classical antiquity|Greek and Roman antiquity]] without citation of [[primary sources]]. 

==External links==
* [https://books.google.com/books?id=Y1sbAAAAMAAJ&hl=iw&pg=PR1#v=onepage&q&f=false ''The Classical Gazetteer: A Dictionary of Ancient Geography, Sacred and Profane'', Whittaker, 1851] on [[Google Books]]

